Defendant Trayvon D Taylor in court with attorney Louis Edward Epps.  Defendant Trayvon D Taylor in custody.  
Matthew James Torbenson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing hearing proceeded.  PSI Report reviewed with the parties.  Statement made by the state, defense, Toya D., and defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1: The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 3 1/2  YEARS with 60 DAYS credit. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 1 1/2 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 2 YEARS.

AS TO COUNT 3:  Defendant to serve 6 MONTHS CONSECUTIVE to Count 1.
AS TO COUNT 4:  Defendant to serve 6 MONTHS CONCURRENT.

The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program AND Substance Abuse Program.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Urine screens;
 - Mental health assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - Participate in Anger management counseling;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - No contact with victims Monica L., Anthony W., Trevion B., or co-actors Dashod Crutchfield and Dvontay Goodwin;
 - Obtain GED or HSED;
 -Pay all supervision fees;
 -Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
 -Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs as to all three counts; 

The Court ordered that all financial obligations be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.  The Court advised the defendant of his determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant.  
Appeal rights given.  Defendant remanded into custody.
